Task 2: Installing Ros into Jetson nano
 
 1.Set locale

We should make sure that we have locale supports that UTF-8

locale  
sudo apt update && sudo apt install locales 
sudo locale-gen en_US en_US.UTF-8  
sudo update-locale LC_ALL=en_US.UTF-8 LANG=en_US.UTF-8  
export LANG=en_US.UTF-8  

2. Setup sources
apt-cache policy | grep universe

Enable the U repository through these instructions.
sudo apt install software-properties-common
sudo add-apt-repository universe

Adding ROS2 repository to the system

sudo apt update && sudo apt install curl gnupg2 lsb-release
sudo curl -sSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ros/rosdistro/master/ros.key  -o /usr/share/keyrings/ros-archive-keyring.gpg

5. Add the repository to the sources list

echo "deb [arch=$(dpkg --print-architecture) signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/ros-archive-keyring.gpg] http://packages.ros.org/ros2/ubuntu $(source /etc/os-release && echo $UBUNTU_CODENAME) main" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/ros2.list > /dev/null

6. Installing the ROS2 packages:

update the apt repository

sudo apt update

upgrade:

sudo apt upgrade

Desktop Install:
sudo apt install ros-foxy-desktop

ROS-Base Install (Bare Bones): 

sudo apt install ros-foxy-ros-base

Setup the enviroment
Bash:

echo "source /opt/ros/foxy/setup.bash" >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc

Zsh:

echo "source /opt/ros/foxy/setup.zsh" >> ~/.zshrc
source ~/.zshrc
